3
1 (3) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection and
2 subsection (4), a special election shall must be held on a regular
3 election date. A special election called by the governor under
4 section 145, 178, 632, 633, or 634 to fill a vacancy or called by
5 the legislature to submit a proposed constitutional amendment as
6 authorized in section 1 of article XII of the state constitution of
7 1963 may, but is not required to be, held on a regular election
8 date.
9 (4) A school district may call a special election to submit a
10 ballot question to borrow money, increase a millage, or establish a
11 bond if an initiative petition is filed with the county clerk. The
12 petition shall must be signed by a number of qualified and
13 registered electors of the district equal to not less than 10% of
14 the electors voting in the last gubernatorial election in that
15 district or 3,000 signatures, whichever number is lesser. less.
16 Section 488 applies to a petition to call a special election for a
17 school district under this section. In addition to the requirements
18 set forth in section 488, the proposed date of the special election
19 shall must appear beneath the petition heading, and the petition
20 shall must clearly state the amount of the millage increase or the
21 amount of the loan or bond sought and the purpose for the millage
22 increase or the purpose for the loan or bond. The petition shall
23 must be filed with the county clerk by 4 p.m. of the twelfth
24 Tuesday before the proposed date of the special election. The
25 petition signatures shall must be obtained within 60 days before
26 the filing of the petition. Any signatures obtained more than 60
27 days before the filing of the petition are not valid. If the
28 special election called by the school district is not scheduled to
29 be held on a regular election date as provided in subsection (1),
STM H02958'25 a (H-1) b1nqh8

4
1 the special election shall must be held on a Tuesday. A special
2 election called by a school district under this subsection shall
3 must not be held within 30 days before or 35 days after a regular
4 election date as provided in subsection (1). A school district may
5 only call 1 special election pursuant to under this subsection in
6 each calendar year. Beginning January 1, 2027, this subsection is
7 subject to the limitation in section 24f(4) of the general property
8 tax act, 1893 PA 206, MCL 211.24f.
9 (5) The secretary of state shall direct and supervise the
10 consolidation of all elections held under this act.
11 (6) This section shall be known and may be cited known as the
12 "Hammerstrom election consolidation law".
13 Sec. 821. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2), the board
14 of county canvassers shall meet at the office of the county clerk
15 no later than 9 a.m. on the Thursday after any election held in the
16 county. The county clerk or the county clerk's staff shall
17 determine the meeting date and time for the board of county
18 canvassers.
19 (2) If, Subject to this subsection, if, at an election held on
20 the May regular election date, a ballot question appears on the
21 ballot concerning an authorized millage that is subject to a
22 millage reduction as provided in section 34d of the general
23 property tax act, 1893 PA 206, MCL 211.34d, the board of county
24 canvassers shall meet to canvass and certify the results of the
25 vote on that proposition after May 31 and before June 15 following
26 the election. Beginning January 1, 2027, this subsection is subject
27 to the limitation in section 24f(4) of the general property tax
28 act, 1893 PA 206, MCL 211.24f.
